-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Constellation Brands, Cree, Newfield Exploration
-- 
-- Thu Jul 03, 2014 01:45AM EDT
-- None



July 3 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including Chatham Lodging Trust, Cree and Newfield Exploration, on Thursday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Chatham Lodging Trust <CLDT.N>: Barclays reinstates with overweight * Cree Inc <CREE.O>: Oppenheimer raises to outperform from perform * Newfield Exploration <NFX.N>: SocGen cuts to hold from buy   Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Thursday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. * Calpine Corp <CPN.N>: Jefferies cuts price target to $23 from $24; rating hold * Chatham Lodging Trust <CLDT.N>: Barclays reinstates with overweight; $26 price target  * Coach Inc <COH.N>: Credit Suisse cuts target price to $30 from $39; rating neutral * Constellation Brands <STZ.N>: SocGen raises target price to $85 from $77; rating sell  * Cree Inc <CREE.O>: Oppenheimer raises to outperform from perform * Diamond Foods <DMND.O>: KeyBanc raises target price to $35 from $32; rating buy * Newfield Exploration <NFX.N>: SocGen cuts to hold from buy * Newfield Exploration <NFX.N>: SocGen raises target price to $47 from $42 * PNM Resources <PNM.N>: Jefferies raises price target to $33 from $30.50; rating buy